post_text: Cool example. Happy Friday.
shared_text:
Aaron John Singer is feeling inspired.
February 5, 2018 at 12:15 AM ·

This is Jim Thorpe. Look closely at the photo, you can see that he's wearing different socks and shoes. This wasn't a fashion statement. It was the 1912 Olympics, and Jim, an American Indian from Oklahoma represented the U.S. in track and field. On the morning of his competitions, his shoes were stolen. Luckily, Jim ended up finding two shoes in a garbage can. That's the pair that he's wearing in the photo. But one of the shoes was too big, so he had to wear an extra sock. Wearing these shoes, Jim won two gold medals that day.

This is a perfect reminder that you don't have to resign to the excuses that have held you back. So what if life hasn't been fair? What are you going to do about it today? Whatever you woke up with this morning; stolen shoes, ill health, failed relationships, don't let it stop you from running your race. You can experience more in life if you'll get over the excuses and get on with living. You can have reasons or you can have results and you can't have both.
#HealthIsWealth #NoExcuses

Thank you Thomas Elrod

Putnam County Fair Unionville MO
May 13, 2017 at 2:00 PM ·

For the main event: We're proud to announce that Saturday, September 9th on the main stage will be the band Lonestar!

Known for merging their country roots with strong melodies and rich vocals, Lonestar, has amassed RIAA-certified sales in excess of ten million album units since their national launch in 1995, and achieved ten #1 country hits including "No News" & "Come Crying To Me" and their crossover smash "Amazed" (which was also #1 on the Billboard Hot 100, the first record since 1983's "Islands in the Stream" to top both charts).

The band's awards include a 1999 ACM Single of The Year for "Amazed" (the song also won the Song of the Year award), and the 2001 CMA Vocal Group of the Year.

With over a 100 dates worldwide per year, they are celebrating over 20 years together.

shared_text:
Putnam County Baseball
January 15, 2017 at 11:41 AM ·

Putnam County Baseball is pleased to announce a very unique opportunity for our players, coaches, and fans. We are selling approximately 550 tickets to the Dodgers vs. Cardinals game on Memorial Day, May 29th, at 1:15pm. Immediately following the Cardinals game, the Putnam County Midgets and the Knox County Eagles will play at Busch Stadium on the same field as some of the biggest stars in the game.
Seats are located in the LF Loge and are substantially discounted at $25/ticket. 1 ticket allows access to both the Cardinals and Midgets games. You MUST attend Cardinals game to see Midgets game.
Tickets can be purchased from PC baseball players and coaches. Tickets are not currently in but we are accepting orders that will be filled upon arrival of tickets.
Donations are accepted for those who want to help but will not be able to make it to the game. Any little bit helps us make this dream come true.
Any questions can be directed toward Coach Bailey or Coach Robinson.
Thank you for supporting PC baseball and allowing us this memorable experience.

Putnam County Baseball
January 15, 2017 at 11:41 AM ·

Putnam County Baseball is pleased to announce a very unique opportunity for our players, coaches, and fans. Immediately following the Cardinals game, the Putnam County Midgets and the Knox County Eagles will play at Busch Stadium on the same field as some of the biggest stars in the game.
Seats are located in the LF Loge and are substantially discounted at $25/ticket. 1 ticket allows access to both the Cardinals and Midgets games. You MUST attend Cardinals game to see Midgets game.
Tickets can be purchased from PC baseball players and coaches. Tickets are not currently in but we are accepting orders that will be filled upon arrival of tickets.
Donations are accepted for those who want to help but will not be able to make it to the game. Any little bit helps us make this dream come true.

Thank you for supporting PC baseball and allowing us this memorable experience.

post_text:
A tip for fighting the heat and expensive electric bill!

Do not adjust your thermostat to a colder setting than normal with this heat wave. It will not cool your home any faster and could result in excessive cooling there for spending more moolah. =) You don't want that.
